## 3. Class Diagram

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class MainWindow {
        -QLabel video_label
        -QPushButton upload_btn
        -QPushButton camera_btn
        -QPushButton start_btn
        -QPushButton stop_tracking_btn
        -QPushButton stop_btn
        -VideoCapture cap
        -QTimer timer
        -YOLO model
        -DeepSort tracker
        -float conf_threshold
        -bool tracking_enabled
        +__init__()
        +open_video()
        +use_camera()
        +start_tracking()
        +stop_tracking()
        +stop_video()
        +process_frame(frame) frame
        +update_frame()
    }

    MainWindow --|> QMainWindow : inherits
    MainWindow --> YOLO : uses
    MainWindow --> DeepSort : uses
    MainWindow --> QTimer : owns
    MainWindow --> VideoCapture : owns
```

---

## 4. Data-Flow Sequence Diagram

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant GUI as PySide6 GUI
    participant Timer as QTimer (30ms)
    participant Cap as cv2.VideoCapture
    participant YOLO as YOLOv8n
    participant DS as DeepSORT
    participant CV as OpenCV Draw

    User->>GUI: Click "Upload Video" / "Use Camera"
    GUI->>Cap: VideoCapture(source)
    GUI->>Timer: timer.start(30)

    User->>GUI: Click "Start Tracking"
    GUI->>GUI: tracking_enabled = True

    loop Every 30ms
        Timer->>GUI: timeout signal → update_frame()
        GUI->>Cap: cap.read()
        Cap-->>GUI: (ret, frame)
        alt ret == True AND tracking ON
            GUI->>YOLO: model(frame, conf=0.4)
            YOLO-->>GUI: results.boxes [xyxy, conf, cls]
            GUI->>GUI: Convert xyxy → xywh detections list
            GUI->>DS: update_tracks(detections, frame)
            DS-->>GUI: confirmed tracks [ltrb, track_id]
            GUI->>CV: rectangle() + putText() per track
            CV-->>GUI: annotated frame
        end
        GUI->>GUI: cvtColor BGR→RGB
        GUI->>GUI: QImage → QPixmap
        GUI->>GUI: video_label.setPixmap()
    end

    User->>GUI: Click "Stop Tracking"
    GUI->>GUI: tracking_enabled = False

    User->>GUI: Click "Stop Video"
    GUI->>Timer: timer.stop()
    GUI->>Cap: cap.release()
```

---

## 5. State Machine

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle : App launched

    Idle --> VideoPlaying : open_video() / use_camera()
    VideoPlaying --> TrackingActive : start_tracking()
    TrackingActive --> VideoPlaying : stop_tracking()
    VideoPlaying --> Idle : stop_video()
    TrackingActive --> Idle : stop_video()

    state VideoPlaying {
        [*] --> ReadFrame
        ReadFrame --> DisplayRaw : ret=True
        DisplayRaw --> ReadFrame : timer tick
        ReadFrame --> ResetToStart : ret=False
        ResetToStart --> ReadFrame : timer tick
    }

    state TrackingActive {
        [*] --> ReadFrame2 : read frame
        ReadFrame2 --> YOLODetect : ret=True
        YOLODetect --> DeepSORTTrack
        DeepSORTTrack --> DrawAnnotations
        DrawAnnotations --> DisplayFrame
        DisplayFrame --> ReadFrame2 : timer tick
        ReadFrame2 --> ResetLoop : ret=False
        ResetLoop --> ReadFrame2 : timer tick
    }
```

