## 6. File-Level Implementation Breakdown

### [main.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py) — Method-by-Method Reference

| Method | Lines | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| [__init__](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py#16-81) | 16–80 | Window setup, UI layout, model/tracker init, signal wiring |
| [open_video](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py#83-89) | 83–88 | Opens file dialog → sets `VideoCapture` → starts timer |
| [use_camera](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py#90-94) | 90–93 | Opens webcam (index 0) → starts timer |
| [start_tracking](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py#95-97) | 95–96 | Sets `tracking_enabled = True` |
| [stop_tracking](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py#98-100) | 98–99 | Sets `tracking_enabled = False` |
| [stop_video](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py#101-106) | 101–105 | Stops timer, releases capture, resets label |
| [process_frame](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py#108-146) | 108–145 | YOLO inference → detection conversion → DeepSORT update → drawing |
| [update_frame](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py#148-170) | 148–169 | Timer callback: read → optional track → BGR→RGB → display |
| `__main__` block | 172–178 | Creates `QApplication`, shows window, enters event loop |

---

## 7. Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **CPU-only mode** (`model.to("cpu")`) | Ensures zero-GPU portability on any machine |
| **QTimer at 30ms** | ~33 FPS cap; balances smoothness vs CPU load |
| **Infinite video loop** (`CAP_PROP_POS_FRAMES → 0`) | Video replays indefinitely until manually stopped |
| **conf_threshold = 0.4** | Filters out low-confidence ghost detections |
| **DeepSORT (max_age=20, n_init=3)** | Keeps track alive 20 frames without match; needs 3 hits to confirm |
| **xyxy → xywh conversion** | DeepSORT expects `[x, y, width, height]` format |

